Interface SteganoStrategy

All Known Implementing Classes:
InAudioStrategy, InPictureStrategy
public interface SteganoStrategy

The SteganoStrategy Interface needs to be implemented by all different Stegano Algorithms.

Method Detail

runHide

void runHide(File inModBaseFile,
             File inBaseFile,
             File inHiddenFile,
             byte pollution)
             throws Exception
This Method is called by the Controller to run the Staganographie Algorithm of the specific Strategy and hide the inHiddenFile in the inBaseFile

Parameters:
inModBaseFile - the File, where the results are saved to.
inBaseFile - The BaseFile on which the Algorithm will process the hiding.
inHiddenFile - The File to hide.
pollution - The nummber [1-7] of Bits in a Byte which are manipulated by the Algorithm to hide the information. Increasing pollution increases the amount of size for the HiddenFile
Throws:
Exception

runSeek

String runSeek(File inModBaseFile,
               String inHiddenFileSaveDir)
               throws Exception
This Method is called by the Controller to run the Staganographie Algorithm of the specific Strategy which will seek the hidden Information in the modified BaseFile.

Parameters:
inBaseFile - The BaseFile on which the Algorithm will process and seek for hidden Information/File.
inHiddenFileSaveDir - The directory where the Hiddenfile will be saved.
Returns:
is the absolute Filepath to the Hiddenfile, the Steganographie-Algorithm found in the modified BaseFile.
Throws:
Exception

getFormatedBaseFileHexString

List<String> getFormatedBaseFileHexString()
This method returns a List with the hexadecimal String representation of the Elements (this could be: Integer, Long or Byte), which are read from the Basefile in the specific Stegano Algorithm.

Returns:
a List with a hexadecimal String representation of each processed Element.

getFormatedModBaseFileHexString

List<String> getFormatedModBaseFileHexString()
This method returns a List with the hexadecimal String representation of the Elements (this could be: Integer, Long or Byte), which are modiefied/processed by the specific Stegano Algorithm. Each Element in the returned List corresponds to the Element with the same Index in getFormatedBaseFileHexString(). Moreover the difference between the two corresponding elements, represents the modifications made by the Stegano Algorithm.

Returns:
a List with a hexadecimal String representation of each processed Element.
